Let $T(n)$ be the number of incongruent triangles with integral sides and
perimeter $n >= 6$. Prove that $T(n) = T(n - 3)$ if $n$ is even, or disprove by
a counterexample. (Note: two triangles are _congruent_ if there is a one-to-one
correspondence between the sides of the two triangles such that corresponding
sides have the same length.)
